In Hong Kong, a two-year-old boy recovered from the H5N1 strain of influenza, while a three-year-old boy and a man died.
A 13-year-old girl is hospitalized with the disease.
Hospitals and clinics are testing patients for the flu, with relatives showing flu-like symptoms.
Macao residents are urged to stay calm as no bird flu cases have been reported.
Chicken sales have dropped, but experts assure the safety of imported poultry.
Hong Kong is coordinating efforts to prevent the spread of the virus, with confirmed and suspected cases increasing.
Shenzhen has not found any H5N1 cases among its poultry farms.
